WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.084 --> 00:00:02.187
-I kissed Elle.
-I don't want to look at you.

2
00:00:02.211 --> 00:00:04.648
I don't want to be around you.
and you can tell Elle

3
00:00:04.672 --> 00:00:05.982
I am done with her. too.

4
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:08.068
I don't want to lose Shannon as a friend.

5
00:00:08.092 --> 00:00:09.653
Previously on Elle...

6
00:00:09.677 --> 00:00:10.696
It's my mom.

7
00:00:10.720 --> 00:00:11.988
They were there to arrest her.

8
00:00:12.012 --> 00:00:14.825
Thousands of dollars in cash
was reported stolen from school today.

9
00:00:14.849 --> 00:00:16.368
They found it in her car.

10
00:00:16.392 --> 00:00:17.661
You don't need to come
to your own defense

11
00:00:17.685 --> 00:00:18.853
if we do it for you.

12
00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:23.941
It's everything we got
from Anderson's office.

13
00:00:25.109 --> 00:00:27.587
What if the receipts aren't real?

14
00:00:27.611 --> 00:00:29.005
Principal Anderson

15
00:00:29.029 --> 00:00:31.341
was stealing money
because he was being blackmailed

16
00:00:31.365 --> 00:00:33.593
for his secret.

17
00:00:33.617 --> 00:00:35.053
But by whom?

18
00:00:35.077 --> 00:00:38.140
Mayoral hopeful Dean Wilson.

19
00:00:38.164 --> 00:00:41.292
you picked the wrong student body
to mess with.

20
00:00:43.878 --> 00:00:46.464
E-L-L-E. That's how we...

21
00:00:48.674 --> 00:00:49.735
She's back?

22
00:00:49.759 --> 00:00:50.902
Shannon?

23
00:00:50.926 --> 00:00:53.572
Turns out.
sweet. innocent Elle Woods

24
00:00:53.596 --> 00:00:57.349
is nothing more
than a backstabbing blond bitch.

25
00:01:03.814 --> 00:01:05.834
I think everyone
would like to hear more

26
00:01:05.858 --> 00:01:07.902
from the great Elle Woods.

27
00:01:09.236 --> 00:01:11.631
Uh. look. whatever you're about
to read right now.

28
00:01:11.655 --> 00:01:13.467
I wrote it a long time ago.

29
00:01:13.491 --> 00:01:15.510
I never thought they'd actually print it.

30
00:01:15.534 --> 00:01:17.387
I'm sorry.
these logistics are fascinating.

31
00:01:17.411 --> 00:01:19.598
but what is it she actually wrote?

32
00:01:19.622 --> 00:01:22.476
Basically. we were a hardship
she had to overcome.

33
00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:25.645
We're not as privileged as she is.

34
00:01:25.669 --> 00:01:28.857
We're so focused on justice

35
00:01:28.881 --> 00:01:31.175
that we don't care
that we dress like crap.

36
00:01:32.468 --> 00:01:34.821
But don't worry.
she makes sure everyone knows

37
00:01:34.845 --> 00:01:38.867
it's not our fault that we don't have
the access to the things that she does.

38
00:01:38.891 --> 00:01:43.163
"What I've learned is to treat everyone
with love and kindness.

39
00:01:43.187 --> 00:01:46.315
even if they don't have
a skin care routine."

40
00:01:47.900 --> 00:01:50.045
It's not like anyone
was rolling out

41
00:01:50.069 --> 00:01:51.880
the welcome wagon for me when I got here.

42
00:01:51.904 --> 00:01:55.217
I mean. you all prejudged me. too.

43
00:01:55.241 --> 00:01:57.636
Was Donna mean to you. too?

44
00:01:57.660 --> 00:01:59.596
Because. according to these.
when you got Donna fired.

45
00:01:59.620 --> 00:02:01.014
you didn't care about her job.

46
00:02:01.038 --> 00:02:03.099
You cared about your own "comeback."

47
00:02:03.123 --> 00:02:04.684
-Well...
-And all that shit

48
00:02:04.708 --> 00:02:07.187
about clearing Donna's name?

49
00:02:07.211 --> 00:02:08.605
You just cared about looking like a hero

50
00:02:08.629 --> 00:02:10.816
in front of the school
and all those cameras.

51
00:02:10.840 --> 00:02:13.109
Well. now we know why your mom
was filming everything.

52
00:02:13.133 --> 00:02:15.445
It wasn't like that. I...

53
00:02:15.469 --> 00:02:19.014
I just wanted to show I can make
a positive impact somewhere.

54
00:02:20.975 --> 00:02:24.037
I-I don't know. Elle's...

55
00:02:24.061 --> 00:02:25.664
also been pretty loyal.

56
00:02:25.688 --> 00:02:29.084
I mean. she's annoyingly dependable.

57
00:02:29.108 --> 00:02:30.627
"Loyal"

58
00:02:30.651 --> 00:02:32.921
is an interesting word.

59
00:02:32.945 --> 00:02:35.757
Because this is a person
who also kissed Miles...

60
00:02:35.781 --> 00:02:37.992
the night my mom died.

61
00:02:39.618 --> 00:02:40.995
Are you for real?

62
00:02:43.330 --> 00:02:45.308
I know this all sounds bad. but...

63
00:02:45.332 --> 00:02:47.334
It sounds bad because it is bad.

64
00:02:52.715 --> 00:02:54.800
Please believe me. I want to be here.

65
00:02:57.636 --> 00:02:59.722
Seattle doesn't want you here.

66
00:03:06.228 --> 00:03:09.457
I want you
to choose something for both of us.

67
00:03:09.481 --> 00:03:11.126
Why don't you just tell me
what you want to watch

68
00:03:11.150 --> 00:03:12.919
instead of trying to make me guess?

69
00:03:12.943 --> 00:03:15.005
Here's a hint: it's not Road House.

70
00:03:15.029 --> 00:03:17.048
Which we've watched. what.
a hundred times?

71
00:03:17.072 --> 00:03:19.426
-You love Road House.
-No. you love Road House.

72
00:03:19.450 --> 00:03:20.844
and I go along with it.

73
00:03:20.868 --> 00:03:22.178
That's not the same thing.

74
00:03:22.202 --> 00:03:24.014
I can't watch Patrick Swayze

75
00:03:24.038 --> 00:03:26.433
rip someone's throat out one more time.

76
00:03:26.457 --> 00:03:28.602
Oh. hey. honey.
We were just having a little...

77
00:03:28.626 --> 00:03:30.377
Do you even realize what you've done?

78
00:03:31.337 --> 00:03:34.774
I... Okay. I hear your point.
but we were both fighting.

79
00:03:34.798 --> 00:03:37.193
This isn't about you and Dad.
Who cares about Dad?

80
00:03:37.217 --> 00:03:38.719
Hey.

81
00:03:39.345 --> 00:03:40.989
Yeah. you're right. No.

82
00:03:41.013 --> 00:03:43.450
Not-not the time to dissect that.

83
00:03:43.474 --> 00:03:44.767
I'm gonna go.

84
00:03:48.938 --> 00:03:51.750
I know you submitted my Cosmo application.

85
00:03:51.774 --> 00:03:54.693
after I specifically told you
I didn't want to apply.

86
00:03:55.277 --> 00:03:56.463
It doesn't even matter that I won.

87
00:03:56.487 --> 00:03:58.131
-because everything else is gone...
-What? You won?

88
00:03:58.155 --> 00:04:00.449
Oh. my God. that's am...

89
00:04:01.283 --> 00:04:02.594
awful.

90
00:04:02.618 --> 00:04:05.889
I was finally making progress here.
and you threw it away.

91
00:04:05.913 --> 00:04:08.183
I was just trying
to give you some options.

92
00:04:08.207 --> 00:04:11.227
Well. it seems like option A
is everyone hates me

93
00:04:11.251 --> 00:04:13.605
and option B is everyone really hates me.

94
00:04:13.629 --> 00:04:15.231
And they should.

95
00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:16.775
