254
00:12:55.484 --> 00:12:57.003
Heather Locklear.

255
00:12:57.027 --> 00:12:58.296
Okay. pinch me.

256
00:12:58.320 --> 00:12:59.839
Ah!

257
00:12:59.863 --> 00:13:02.425
Your homework for tomorrow

258
00:13:02.449 --> 00:13:04.802
will be to present me
with different accessories

259
00:13:04.826 --> 00:13:06.721
that you think could work for Heather.

260
00:13:06.745 --> 00:13:08.806
You're all here for a reason.

261
00:13:08.830 --> 00:13:11.166
Now it's time for you to prove it.

262
00:13:13.376 --> 00:13:14.854
Do you think that Patrick Swayze

263
00:13:14.878 --> 00:13:16.063
will be there?

264
00:13:16.087 --> 00:13:18.316
-I hope so.
-Oh. my God.

265
00:13:18.340 --> 00:13:21.551
I might actually lose my mind.

266
00:13:23.303 --> 00:13:25.031
Does this say
"Golden Globes party"?

267
00:13:25.055 --> 00:13:28.242
Mm. no. that feels more
People's Choice.

268
00:13:28.266 --> 00:13:30.161
Ooh. what about this
for your Cosmo homework?

269
00:13:30.185 --> 00:13:33.039
I love that. Who's the designer?

270
00:13:33.063 --> 00:13:36.900
Eh. I heard they have
unethical labor practices.

271
00:13:37.901 --> 00:13:39.027
What?

272
00:13:40.028 --> 00:13:42.548
Uh. never mind.
I don't know why I said that.

273
00:13:42.572 --> 00:13:44.258
Must be a Seattle thing.

274
00:13:44.282 --> 00:13:46.260
Yeah.
Seattle can get to your head like that.

275
00:13:46.284 --> 00:13:47.970
Yeah. Madison was only there a few days

276
00:13:47.994 --> 00:13:50.014
before she started making out
with some activist guy.

277
00:13:50.038 --> 00:13:51.641
What?

278
00:13:51.665 --> 00:13:53.601
She didn't know.

279
00:13:53.625 --> 00:13:55.353
Oh. I mean...

280
00:13:55.377 --> 00:13:58.880
maybe that happened.
but also. I-I could be wrong.

281
00:14:02.842 --> 00:14:05.679
Maybe you guys could find
that purse in a vegan leather?

282
00:14:10.392 --> 00:14:13.728
Yeah. that purse doesn't
come in a vegan leather.

283
00:14:15.188 --> 00:14:16.815
You kissed Dustin?

284
00:14:18.900 --> 00:14:20.485
Yes.

285
00:14:22.529 --> 00:14:23.798
Um...

286
00:14:23.822 --> 00:14:25.716
Uh. why didn't you tell me?

287
00:14:25.740 --> 00:14:27.552
Well. we were fighting.

288
00:14:27.576 --> 00:14:29.637
Which would have been bad enough. but...

289
00:14:29.661 --> 00:14:33.933
considering we were fighting about
how much you had been withholding from me.

290
00:14:33.957 --> 00:14:36.960
I don't know. maybe there was
some tit for tat in there?

291
00:14:39.254 --> 00:14:41.607
I'm sorry. I should've told you.

292
00:14:41.631 --> 00:14:46.153
But I don't want to keep things
from each other anymore.

293
00:14:46.177 --> 00:14:48.698
I feel like we just got back
to a good place.

294
00:14:48.722 --> 00:14:50.557
Yeah. we have.

295
00:14:51.891 --> 00:14:55.246
In the spirit of being honest
with each other. can I ask you something?

296
00:14:55.270 --> 00:14:57.123
Of course.

297
00:14:57.147 --> 00:14:59.625
Based on your face and your whole...

298
00:14:59.649 --> 00:15:02.169
everything. right now...

299
00:15:02.193 --> 00:15:04.279
do you have a crush on Dustin?

300
00:15:05.280 --> 00:15:07.741
Uh... no.

301
00:15:09.367 --> 00:15:10.702
I don't.

302
00:15:11.453 --> 00:15:15.891
I mean. if anyone in Seattle
was crush material. it was Miles.

303
00:15:15.915 --> 00:15:18.835
I just feel bad that I made you feel like
you couldn't tell me things.

304
00:15:19.919 --> 00:15:22.064
I should have fought harder
for our friendship.

305
00:15:22.088 --> 00:15:24.775
Okay. well. I could have been
more understanding when I came to visit.

306
00:15:24.799 --> 00:15:27.445
Well. I could be more understanding
that you were less understanding.

307
00:15:27.469 --> 00:15:29.471
-Aww.
-Oh...

308
00:15:30.722 --> 00:15:32.140
Elle.

309
00:15:36.227 --> 00:15:37.371
Are you sure you don't like him?

310
00:15:37.395 --> 00:15:40.833
He's running around
kissing my best friend.

311
00:15:40.857 --> 00:15:43.502
Clearly. I don't know him
as well as I thought.

312
00:15:43.526 --> 00:15:45.504
Good morning. students.

313
00:15:45.528 --> 00:15:48.215
Today's announcements
start with some bad news.

314
00:15:48.239 --> 00:15:51.010
As your interim principal.
I've had to make the very hard decision

315
00:15:51.034 --> 00:15:53.387
to cancel winter formal.

316
00:15:53.411 --> 00:15:56.140
Now. the school board is still
in the process of digging itself out

317
00:15:56.164 --> 00:16:00.353
of the financial hole
some recent events have put us in.

318
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:03.481
Now. I know this isn't the outcome
that you all would have hoped.

319
00:16:03.505 --> 00:16:07.008
Uh. and that concludes
this morning's announcements.

320
00:16:08.009 --> 00:16:10.689
Dude. does this mean we can suck
the helium out of the balloon arch?

321
00:16:14.182 --> 00:16:15.392
Have you heard from her again?

322
00:16:16.518 --> 00:16:17.727
No.

323
00:16:19.145 --> 00:16:23.376
She reached out a few times
after she left. but. uh. I wasn't ready.

324
00:16:23.400 --> 00:16:27.904
I mean. I always thought
she'd dump us for L.A.. and here we are.

325
00:16:29.197 --> 00:16:31.175
We can just go back
to the status quo now. right?

326
00:16:31.199 --> 00:16:34.178
It's kind of messed up that she just left
without saying goodbye. though.

327
00:16:34.202 --> 00:16:37.682
Sure. we were all mad at her and weren't
talking to her. but she just bailed.

328
00:16:37.706 --> 00:16:39.016
-Mm-hmm.
-I guess now she can go

329
00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:40.768
to her precious Golden Globes. though.

330
00:16:40.792 --> 00:16:42.603
-Right.
-What?

331
00:16:42.627 --> 00:16:46.399
Normally. I only see you this fired up
about. like. Freeing Tibet.

332
00:16:46.423 --> 00:16:47.608
So?

333
00:16:47.632 --> 00:16:50.152
So. I wonder if you. perhaps.

334
00:16:50.176 --> 00:16:53.572
are having this reaction
because you miss her?

335
00:16:53.596 --> 00:16:56.725
I wonder if you should.
perhaps. stop talking.

336
00:16:58.393 --> 00:17:00.538
Bet you didn't have
morning coffees on the quad in Seattle.

337
00:17:00.562 --> 00:17:02.123
I think that "coffee"

338
00:17:02.147 --> 00:17:04.917
is the only part of that sentence
that existed in Seattle.

339
00:17:04.941 --> 00:17:06.502
You didn't have mornings?

340
00:17:06.526 --> 00:17:08.629
-Well... Oh.
-Oh.

341
00:17:08.653 --> 00:17:09.880
Hey.

342
00:17:09.904 --> 00:17:10.965
Hi.

343
00:17:10.989 --> 00:17:12.258
He just said hi to you.

344
00:17:12.282 --> 00:17:13.509
-And you said hi back.
-That's basically third base.

345
00:17:13.533 --> 00:17:15.136
You'll be kissing in no time.

346
00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:17.388
three-point plan style.

347
00:17:17.412 --> 00:17:19.265
Oh. maybe it could even happen
at the pre-Golden Globes party.

348
00:17:19.289 --> 00:17:22.017
He's gonna be there.
His aunt did the set design on Cybill.

349
00:17:22.041 --> 00:17:23.519
Ooh. that'll give you guys
time to figure out

350
00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:25.646
your best couple angles
for prom portraits.

351
00:17:25.670 --> 00:17:27.815
I-I can't believe
that it's already prom season.

352
00:17:27.839 --> 00:17:30.609
Like. didn't we just have winter formal
before the holiday break?

353
00:17:30.633 --> 00:17:32.945
Oh. my God. Winter formal.

354
00:17:32.969 --> 00:17:34.029
Oh. you didn't miss much.

355
00:17:34.053 --> 00:17:35.489
Chad and Becca broke up again.

356
00:17:35.513 --> 00:17:37.324
-Then they got back together again.
-Mm-hmm.

357
00:17:37.348 --> 00:17:39.869
No. I totally forgot to tell Donna
about a balloon arch

358
00:17:39.893 --> 00:17:42.520
I had ordered to Rainier West for our...

359
00:17:43.646 --> 00:17:46.125
their winter formal.

360
00:17:46.149 --> 00:17:48.335
I hope someone signed for it.

361
00:17:48.359 --> 00:17:50.588
I should have told them
to position it on the west wall

362
00:17:50.612 --> 00:17:53.257
for the most dramatic entry experience
before I left.

363
00:17:53.281 --> 00:17:54.675
I'm sure it's fine.

364
00:17:54.699 --> 00:17:57.803
Can't they figure out
their own balloon arch logistics?

365
00:17:57.827 --> 00:17:59.305
You're right.

366
00:17:59.329 --> 00:18:01.331
I just don't like leaving
odds and ends undone.

367
00:18:03.833 --> 00:18:05.227
Hey. Dad.

368
00:18:05.251 --> 00:18:07.313
Miles. Guess who's here.

369
00:18:07.337 --> 00:18:08.564
Oh.

370
00:18:08.588 --> 00:18:10.441
Mr. Woods. Hi.

371
00:18:10.465 --> 00:18:13.611
Your dads have been so nice.
inviting me over so much

372
00:18:13.635 --> 00:18:15.970
now that Eva and Elle are gone.

373
00:18:16.471 --> 00:18:18.324
-Oh. I just spoke to Elle.
-Yeah?

374
00:18:18.348 --> 00:18:20.367
-Yeah.
-How-how is she?

375
00:18:20.391 --> 00:18:22.453
Hmm? Oh. well. you know.

376
00:18:22.477 --> 00:18:24.747
she's... great.

377
00:18:24.771 --> 00:18:26.123
You know? She loves L.A.

378
00:18:26.147 --> 00:18:27.416
Really sounds like she's thriving there.

379
00:18:27.440 --> 00:18:29.335
-Yeah!
-Mm-hmm.

380
00:18:29.359 --> 00:18:30.544
That's cool.

381
00:18:30.568 --> 00:18:32.379
Yeah. and because of
the whole internship thing.

382
00:18:32.403 --> 00:18:35.549
she gets to go to the Golden Globes.
which has always been her dream.

383
00:18:35.573 --> 00:18:37.343
I am so happy for her.

384
00:18:37.367 --> 00:18:39.470
Even if I can't show my face in L.A.

385
00:18:39.494 --> 00:18:42.205
The whole "persona non grata" thing.

386
00:18:44.040 --> 00:18:48.145
So. uh. has-has she mentioned
anything else or...

387
00:18:48.169 --> 00:18:49.712
you know. like. any-anyone else?

388
00:18:51.339 --> 00:18:53.067
What do you mean?

389
00:18:53.091 --> 00:18:55.027
Like. uh...

390
00:18:55.051 --> 00:18:57.512
I don't know.
anything about Seattle. or...

391
00:18:58.888 --> 00:19:01.659
-Anything?
-Mm. mm-mm.

392
00:19:01.683 --> 00:19:03.160
Check...

393
00:19:03.184 --> 00:19:04.602
this out.

394
00:19:05.603 --> 00:19:06.705
Whoa.

395
00:19:06.729 --> 00:19:07.748
What's with the banner?

396
00:19:07.772 --> 00:19:10.751
Elle approached me
with one of her genius ideas

397
00:19:10.775 --> 00:19:12.277
at the homecoming meet.

398
00:19:13.152 --> 00:19:16.382
Her thought was that small businesses
sponsor the dance.

399
00:19:16.406 --> 00:19:18.509
and that money goes to the support staff.

400
00:19:18.533 --> 00:19:19.742
It's win-win.

401
00:19:20.577 --> 00:19:21.911
That's. uh...

402
00:19:22.912 --> 00:19:24.539
not a bad idea.

403
00:19:26.457 --> 00:19:27.852
Hey. Can we talk?

404
00:19:27.876 --> 00:19:30.563
Well. you just cut me.
so we're not off to a great start.

405
00:19:30.587 --> 00:19:31.772
Okay. whatever. Look.

406
00:19:31.796 --> 00:19:33.649
I have some intel.
seems kind of like a you thing.

407
00:19:33.673 --> 00:19:35.818
I'm fascinated to see what you think
a "me" thing is.

408
00:19:35.842 --> 00:19:37.027
This is fun.

409
00:19:37.051 --> 00:19:38.761
The thing is about Elle.

410
00:19:39.888 --> 00:19:41.115
Hey. you remember the dance
she was planning?

411
00:19:41.139 --> 00:19:42.640
You mean the one she asked me to?

412
00:19:44.058 --> 00:19:45.244
She asked you?

413
00:19:45.268 --> 00:19:46.662
Yeah.

414
00:19:46.686 --> 00:19:48.706
Clearly. she has good taste.

415
00:19:48.730 --> 00:19:50.356
Okay.

416
00:19:52.859 --> 00:19:56.505
So. I guess her whole thing was.
it wasn't really even about being a dance.

417
00:19:56.529 --> 00:19:59.758
It was a fundraiser for the support staff.
which would've helped even more now.

418
00:19:59.782 --> 00:20:02.928
since they got boned
by Principal Anderson and Dean.

419
00:20:02.952 --> 00:20:04.763
All right. look. I know
the dance was canceled.

420
00:20:04.787 --> 00:20:07.349
but doesn't it seem like
she was on to something?

421
00:20:07.373 --> 00:20:09.310
Unfortunately. yes. It's a good idea.

422
00:20:09.334 --> 00:20:12.313
I mean. not the dancing part

423
00:20:12.337 --> 00:20:14.773
or the school-sanctioned part
or any of Elle Woodsy stuff.

424
00:20:14.797 --> 00:20:16.901
but the fundraising. that's good.

425
00:20:16.925 --> 00:20:18.527
So. should we do that?

426
00:20:18.551 --> 00:20:20.863
-We could call Elle.
-No.

427
00:20:20.887 --> 00:20:23.866
We wouldn't do the Elle version.

428
00:20:23.890 --> 00:20:27.077
What's the one thing everyone
at this school agrees is worthwhile?

429
00:20:27.101 --> 00:20:28.227
CarpetMart.

430
00:20:28.853 --> 00:20:30.789
We could ask Bob's Your Uncle to perform.
and donate the proceeds?

431
00:20:30.813 --> 00:20:33.500
I mean. it'd basically be like
our version of Live Aid.

432
00:20:33.524 --> 00:20:35.961
Except for school secretaries
instead of famine.

433
00:20:35.985 --> 00:20:37.195
Yep. that's good.

434
00:20:38.196 --> 00:20:41.258
We could call it our "Winter Informal."

435
00:20:41.282 --> 00:20:43.135
-Let's do it.
-Liz. you're good at zines.

436
00:20:43.159 --> 00:20:44.929
so we'll put you in charge of the flyers.

437
00:20:44.953 --> 00:20:46.805
Uh. I'm good at getting
the word out. so I'll do that.

438
00:20:46.829 --> 00:20:50.976
And you can. I don't know. uh.
sweet-talk all the local businesses

439
00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:53.044
into sponsoring the event.

440
00:20:53.628 --> 00:20:55.463
And I could provide the drinks.

441
00:20:56.047 --> 00:20:57.799
My parents never lock
their liquor cabinet.

442
00:20:58.466 --> 00:20:59.568
-Great.
-I love that you're doing this

443
00:20:59.592 --> 00:21:00.653
to spite Elle.

444
00:21:00.677 --> 00:21:03.864
I mean. I tried to tell everyone
that L.A. people are entitled.

445
00:21:03.888 --> 00:21:06.283
Let the record state we're doing this
out of a desire to help others.

446
00:21:06.307 --> 00:21:07.701
not to spite Elle Woods.

447
00:21:07.725 --> 00:21:09.119
Exactly.

448
00:21:09.143 --> 00:21:10.454
That's what I was saying.

449
00:21:10.478 --> 00:21:13.165
The important thing
is that we're doing this our way.

450
00:21:13.189 --> 00:21:14.482
Not Elle's.

451
00:21:15.441 --> 00:21:16.776
Not Elle's.

452
00:21:18.361 --> 00:21:20.214
Rainier West High School.

453
00:21:20.238 --> 00:21:21.674
Donna?

454
00:21:21.698 --> 00:21:23.008
Elle Woods!

455
00:21:23.032 --> 00:21:26.178
Hi. I just called to apologize.

456
00:21:26.202 --> 00:21:29.122
There was a balloon arch situation
I completely mishandled.

457
00:21:30.206 --> 00:21:32.518
Uh. yeah. I'm not sure if that's an issue.

458
00:21:32.542 --> 00:21:34.520
No one's talking about it?

459
00:21:34.544 --> 00:21:36.462
Not that I've heard of.

460
00:21:37.588 --> 00:21:39.048
Well. great.

461
00:21:40.383 --> 00:21:43.696
Hey. your dance is back on. baby.

462
00:21:43.720 --> 00:21:46.115
I... didn't know it was off.

463
00:21:46.139 --> 00:21:49.368
Yeah. it was.
but. uh. Liz and Dustin and Miles

464
00:21:49.392 --> 00:21:52.579
and. believe it or not.
Kimberly got it back on track.

465
00:21:52.603 --> 00:21:53.872
Oh.

466
00:21:53.896 --> 00:21:58.961
Yeah. It's less of a dance and more
of a concert at CarpetMart. but

467
00:21:58.985 --> 00:22:00.921
I'm-I'm actually a little fuzzy
on the creative.

468
00:22:00.945 --> 00:22:03.507
But it involves raising money
for the school.

469
00:22:03.531 --> 00:22:06.743
And get this.
They're calling it a Winter Informal.

470
00:22:08.703 --> 00:22:11.140
-That's-that's great.
-Yeah. well.

471
00:22:11.164 --> 00:22:13.958
you know these kids. They always march
to the beat of their own drum.

472
00:22:15.001 --> 00:22:18.022
Yeah. they... definitely do.

473
00:22:18.046 --> 00:22:19.648
Hey. so. how's

474
00:22:19.672 --> 00:22:22.776
your whatchamacallit? Uh. internship?

475
00:22:22.800 --> 00:22:24.945
Oh. uh. it's awesome. actually.

476
00:22:24.969 --> 00:22:26.947
Do you know Heather Locklear?

477
00:22:26.971 --> 00:22:29.241
Um. I'm sorry. Elle. I have to go.

478
00:22:29.265 --> 00:22:31.118
There's a whole blood thing
happening here.

479
00:22:31.142 --> 00:22:34.288
I'm glad you're happy.
This is what you wanted.

480
00:22:34.312 --> 00:22:36.439
Yeah.

481
00:22:47.033 --> 00:22:49.386
-And that goes with that?
-Exactly.

482
00:22:49.410 --> 00:22:51.597
I know her reputation precedes her.
but be prepared

483
00:22:51.621 --> 00:22:53.098
for Anna to be savage.

484
00:22:53.122 --> 00:22:57.019
She once pulled Karl Lagerfeld
out of a cat adoption ceremony

485
00:22:57.043 --> 00:22:59.212
to berate him
for sending her the wrong pants.

486
00:23:01.881 --> 00:23:03.442
Hmm. Not bad.

487
00:23:03.466 --> 00:23:05.444
Thank you.

488
00:23:05.468 --> 00:23:06.945
I'm impressed.

489
00:23:06.969 --> 00:23:11.075
Everyone here is on trend.
which means. you're all on the right path.

490
00:23:11.099 --> 00:23:13.994
You have very similar taste. actually.

491
00:23:14.018 --> 00:23:16.938
We chose well.

492
00:23:21.192 --> 00:23:24.129
Is that a good thing or a bad thing?

493
00:23:24.153 --> 00:23:26.090
That we have the same taste. I mean?

494
00:23:26.114 --> 00:23:27.257
I think it's good.

495
00:23:27.281 --> 00:23:30.868
We're all channeling
our inner and outer Cosmo Girl.

496
00:23:32.328 --> 00:23:33.972
You knocked it out of the park.

497
00:23:33.996 --> 00:23:37.101
I'll be presenting all of your choices
to Anna St. George at the styling session.

498
00:23:37.125 --> 00:23:39.144
My God.

499
00:23:39.168 --> 00:23:41.230
Particularly you. Elle.

500
00:23:41.254 --> 00:23:42.922
You have a real knack for this.

501
00:23:47.552 --> 00:23:51.115
So. how is the Winter Informal
planning going?

502
00:23:51.139 --> 00:23:54.517
Uh. it's pretty complicated.
but we'll figure it out.

503
00:23:55.935 --> 00:23:58.163
Elle called the school.

504
00:23:58.187 --> 00:23:59.706
Hmm.

505
00:23:59.730 --> 00:24:03.877
Yeah. Pretty sure she just wanted to hear
how everything was going at school. but

506
00:24:03.901 --> 00:24:07.005
definitely sounds like
she misses everybody.

507
00:24:07.029 --> 00:24:09.615
Right.

508
00:24:12.493 --> 00:24:13.887
Can I say something?

509
00:24:13.911 --> 00:24:15.454
I have a feeling you will anyway.

510
00:24:16.539 --> 00:24:20.018
She obviously messed up. Big-time.

511
00:24:20.042 --> 00:24:22.354
And I'm not happy
about anybody hurting your feelings.

512
00:24:22.378 --> 00:24:25.899
But do you think
there's a chance that your reaction

513
00:24:25.923 --> 00:24:28.718
to all this isn't even totally about Elle?

514
00:24:29.760 --> 00:24:30.988
I mean. what else could it be about?

515
00:24:31.012 --> 00:24:34.950
Well. sweetie. you have had a fear
of abandonment since you were little.

516
00:24:34.974 --> 00:24:38.287
Justifiably. with your dad and all.

517
00:24:38.311 --> 00:24:41.355
So you think this thing
with Elle just fed into that?

518
00:24:42.648 --> 00:24:45.043
I'm just saying.

519
00:24:45.067 --> 00:24:49.756
maybe one day.
you could cut her the smallest break.

520
00:24:49.780 --> 00:24:55.620
I mean. she did basically save me
from serving three to ten years in jail.

521
00:24:58.664 --> 00:25:00.517
Janet. can you put that rack there?

522
00:25:00.541 --> 00:25:02.769
No. not that rack.
That rack. Over there.

523
00:25:02.793 --> 00:25:04.771
Where is her Tab?

524
00:25:04.795 --> 00:25:07.566
She has to have her room-temperature Tab.

525
00:25:07.590 --> 00:25:09.234
I have it.

526
00:25:09.258 --> 00:25:11.260
Thank you.

527
00:25:13.846 --> 00:25:16.575
We have your first choice look
on the mannequin over there.

528
00:25:16.599 --> 00:25:18.911
And then those accessories
we talked about.

529
00:25:18.935 --> 00:25:23.498
The interns and I found some earrings
that feel pretty perfect.

530
00:25:23.522 --> 00:25:25.792
Can I just say. it's an absolute...?

531
00:25:25.816 --> 00:25:28.170
Oh.

532
00:25:28.194 --> 00:25:29.713
Oh. they're lovely. right?

533
00:25:29.737 --> 00:25:32.674
The only thing more impressive
than the interns' eye for earrings

534
00:25:32.698 --> 00:25:34.885
is maybe my eye for talent.

535
00:25:34.909 --> 00:25:36.803
That...

536
00:25:36.827 --> 00:25:38.597
That was a joke.

537
00:25:38.621 --> 00:25:41.374
Unless you don't... want it to be.

538
00:25:43.042 --> 00:25:44.210
That's nice.

539
00:25:49.382 --> 00:25:50.424
Wait.

540
00:25:53.886 --> 00:25:55.239
I just want to say.

541
00:25:55.263 --> 00:25:58.474
this look is very 1994 Vogue.

542
00:26:02.228 --> 00:26:05.415
This is Elle. our most...

543
00:26:05.439 --> 00:26:10.921
opinionated intern. who I'm sure means
that 1994 Vogue is a great thing.

544
00:26:10.945 --> 00:26:12.673
It is.

545
00:26:12.697 --> 00:26:14.323
But it's also safe.

546
00:26:16.033 --> 00:26:18.720
Can I just...?

547
00:26:18.744 --> 00:26:20.538
Okay.

548
00:26:32.049 --> 00:26:33.426
A Cosmo Girl is fearless.

549
00:26:35.553 --> 00:26:37.447
And I'm sorry.

550
00:26:37.471 --> 00:26:40.850
but everyone in this room is full of fear.

551
00:27:04.123 --> 00:27:06.435
And we'd continue these safety pins
to our mid-thigh

552
00:27:06.459 --> 00:27:08.586
with a sheer lining underneath.

553
00:27:15.134 --> 00:27:19.180
To me. fearless is finding something new.

554
00:27:28.731 --> 00:27:30.524
Good instinct.

555
00:27:34.695 --> 00:27:36.256
Okay. but Pavement

556
00:27:36.280 --> 00:27:37.674
is so much better than
The Smashing Pumpkins.

557
00:27:37.698 --> 00:27:38.925
it is actually insane.

558
00:27:38.949 --> 00:27:40.969
See. that is where you're wrong.

559
00:27:40.993 --> 00:27:42.119
Oh. really?

560
00:27:43.496 --> 00:27:45.498
Ooh. not it.

561
00:27:46.707 --> 00:27:48.727
Let me guess.
You want the new PJ Harvey?

562
00:27:48.751 --> 00:27:51.980
-Obviously.
-Should be in alt rock.

563
00:27:52.004 --> 00:27:54.399
Subsection punk blues.

564
00:27:54.423 --> 00:27:56.151
Sub-subsection female punk blues.

565
00:27:56.175 --> 00:27:58.552
-Hmm.
-And also. right here.

566
00:28:03.182 --> 00:28:04.683
How pissed are you at Elle?

567
00:28:05.768 --> 00:28:08.205
Uh. pretty pissed.

568
00:28:08.229 --> 00:28:10.523
But working on it.

569
00:28:11.607 --> 00:28:13.251
That's generous of you.

570
00:28:13.275 --> 00:28:17.756
Well. my mom pointed out
that my reaction to Elle might be

571
00:28:17.780 --> 00:28:21.218
a tiny bit influenced
by a general fear of abandonment.

572
00:28:21.242 --> 00:28:23.970
With my dad.

573
00:28:23.994 --> 00:28:27.182
With certain people
who hooked up with me at summer camp

574
00:28:27.206 --> 00:28:30.268
and then made sure
no one ever. ever found out.

575
00:28:30.292 --> 00:28:31.627
Would you like a bag?

576
00:28:33.295 --> 00:28:35.297
Not no one.

577
00:28:36.674 --> 00:28:38.050
I told Shannon.

578
00:28:40.094 --> 00:28:41.655
Oh.

579
00:28:41.679 --> 00:28:44.223
I. uh. didn't know that.

580
00:28:45.307 --> 00:28:46.809
Yeah.

581
00:28:49.019 --> 00:28:51.540
Oh. uh. anyway. so I-I really came by

582
00:28:51.564 --> 00:28:52.874
because I have some bad news.

583
00:28:52.898 --> 00:28:55.293
Well. good news disguised as bad news.

584
00:28:55.317 --> 00:28:56.795
Bob's Your Uncle broke up.

585
00:28:56.819 --> 00:28:59.548
so they can't perform at CarpetMart.

586
00:28:59.572 --> 00:29:01.007
So we're screwed.

587
00:29:01.031 --> 00:29:02.634
Yes. I can totally see
how that might be good news.

588
00:29:02.658 --> 00:29:05.262
Can you let me finish?

589
00:29:05.286 --> 00:29:09.915
I was thinking that maybe
you would want to perform instead.

590
00:29:12.376 --> 00:29:14.187
Yeah. in what world?

591
00:29:14.211 --> 00:29:16.106
This one.

592
00:29:16.130 --> 00:29:19.359
The only person who has ever seen me
perform in public is my mom.

593
00:29:19.383 --> 00:29:22.529
And that's because she came home early
one time when I was singing in my room.

594
00:29:22.553 --> 00:29:24.823
Hmm.

595
00:29:24.847 --> 00:29:26.474
But your music's really good.

596
00:29:27.558 --> 00:29:29.244
You haven't heard my music.

597
00:29:29.268 --> 00:29:32.354
Uh. like. only three people
have ever bought that tape. so...

598
00:29:35.691 --> 00:29:36.942
Duh.

599
00:29:39.153 --> 00:29:42.007
Sick. Uh. yeah.

600
00:29:42.031 --> 00:29:44.283
Yeah. it's. uh...

601
00:29:46.952 --> 00:29:48.412
Just think about it.

602
00:29:55.377 --> 00:29:57.647
So. how does it feel to be back?

603
00:29:57.671 --> 00:30:01.776
Vanessa. is there a word
stronger than ecstasy?

604
00:30:01.800 --> 00:30:04.571
-She said. "Good instinct."
-I know.

605
00:30:04.595 --> 00:30:07.449
There was. like. five seconds
I thought I'd gotten myself banned

606
00:30:07.473 --> 00:30:10.202
from the world of fashion
and possibly the world itself for life.

607
00:30:10.226 --> 00:30:12.329
But it was. like.

608
00:30:12.353 --> 00:30:16.291
everything inside of me was telling
to trust my gut and be my own self.

609
00:30:16.315 --> 00:30:18.084
Way to be profound. Elle.

610
00:30:18.108 --> 00:30:19.836
I just kept thinking
about this thing

611
00:30:19.860 --> 00:30:23.048
Liz told me when I went to this pool party
that wasn't actually a pool party.

612
00:30:23.072 --> 00:30:25.157
-in a bikini...
-Liz who ran you out of Seattle?

613
00:30:26.242 --> 00:30:28.553
Yes.

614
00:30:28.577 --> 00:30:30.847
Sort of. It's more nuanced than that.

615
00:30:30.871 --> 00:30:32.581
-Mm.
-Mm.

616
00:30:36.335 --> 00:30:38.021
Is that Heather Locklear?

617
00:30:38.045 --> 00:30:39.940
Oh. hi. Heather.

618
00:30:39.964 --> 00:30:41.483
Oh. my God.
I am addicted to Melrose Place.

619
00:30:41.507 --> 00:30:43.068
Ooh. Elle. we need to go say hi to her.

620
00:30:43.092 --> 00:30:44.444
Uh. more importantly.
Hot Josh at 12.

621
00:30:44.468 --> 00:30:46.238
-Now 11:45.
-Now 12:15.

622
00:30:46.262 --> 00:30:47.572
-Now...
-Scatter.

623
00:30:47.596 --> 00:30:49.908
-Yeah.
-Oh.

624
00:30:49.932 --> 00:30:51.058
Hey.

625
00:30:52.351 --> 00:30:54.311
Do you think we could talk somewhere?

626
00:30:55.396 --> 00:30:56.831
Absolutely.

627
00:30:56.855 --> 00:30:58.857
I just remembered. I have to pee.

628
00:31:03.904 --> 00:31:05.364
Um...

629
00:31:14.248 --> 00:31:16.250
Excuse me.

630
00:31:24.592 --> 00:31:26.385
You can sit.

631
00:31:28.178 --> 00:31:29.406
How did you...?

632
00:31:29.430 --> 00:31:32.266
Please don't draw attention to yourself.
I'm hiding.

633
00:31:41.233 --> 00:31:44.421
Um. who-who are you hiding from?

634
00:31:44.445 --> 00:31:45.904
Everyone.

635
00:31:47.531 --> 00:31:48.782
I'm hiding. too.

636
00:31:50.034 --> 00:31:51.177
Not from everyone.

637
00:31:51.201 --> 00:31:52.721
Just a boy.

638
00:31:52.745 --> 00:31:54.556
Hmm. What's wrong with him? Too short?

639
00:31:54.580 --> 00:31:56.165
Too dumb?

640
00:31:58.167 --> 00:31:59.543
Too expected.

641
00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:03.297
You impressed me the other day.

642
00:32:04.381 --> 00:32:05.984
Wow. That means...

643
00:32:06.008 --> 00:32:08.111
-well. everything.
-You don't have to do that.

644
00:32:08.135 --> 00:32:09.696
-Everyone does that.
-No. no. I...

645
00:32:09.720 --> 00:32:11.823
I mean it. I mean.
your opinion means a lot to me.

646
00:32:11.847 --> 00:32:16.101
Well. you're going to assist me
at the Golden Globes tomorrow.

647
00:32:19.813 --> 00:32:21.708
Oh.

648
00:32:21.732 --> 00:32:24.586
That's typically followed
by a high-pitched scream.

649
00:32:24.610 --> 00:32:27.696
No. trust me. I'm screaming internally.

650
00:32:29.406 --> 00:32:33.553
I've imagined this happening
so many times.

651
00:32:33.577 --> 00:32:36.622
and now it finally is. and...

652
00:32:39.375 --> 00:32:40.751
It feels...

653
00:32:43.253 --> 00:32:44.588
Expected?

654
00:32:49.301 --> 00:32:50.302
Yeah.

655
00:32:51.720 --> 00:32:53.531
It's a long story. but I spent

656
00:32:53.555 --> 00:32:57.434
last semester
somewhere really out of my comfort zone.

657
00:32:59.395 --> 00:33:03.124
It was the first time in my life I felt...

658
00:33:03.148 --> 00:33:04.775
challenged.

659
00:33:06.068 --> 00:33:08.171
And now I'm here. doing what I love.

660
00:33:08.195 --> 00:33:10.715
and it's... not...

661
00:33:10.739 --> 00:33:12.533
challenging.

662
00:33:14.618 --> 00:33:16.846
I have a friend who worked at Perry Ellis.

663
00:33:16.870 --> 00:33:19.099
And. uh. he felt

664
00:33:19.123 --> 00:33:21.935
that people at his fashion house
were playing it a little safe.

665
00:33:21.959 --> 00:33:26.106
So one day. he decided to be fearless.

666
00:33:26.130 --> 00:33:28.108
He went against the grain and sent a line

667
00:33:28.132 --> 00:33:30.860
of flannel and Doc Martens
down the runway.

668
00:33:30.884 --> 00:33:32.529
Critics crucified him.

669
00:33:32.553 --> 00:33:36.408
What kind of idiot
puts a beanie on Kate Moss?

670
00:33:36.432 --> 00:33:38.451
He totally bombed.

671
00:33:38.475 --> 00:33:41.103
And his bosses at Perry Ellis fired him
on the spot.

672
00:33:44.648 --> 00:33:47.109
It was the most compelling runway
I've ever seen.

673
00:33:50.863 --> 00:33:53.073
Sometimes friction means
you're in the right place.

674
00:33:56.285 --> 00:33:57.953
I have to make the rounds.

675
00:34:02.499 --> 00:34:05.937
Before you go.
who is your designer friend?

676
00:34:05.961 --> 00:34:07.546
Marc Jacobs.

677
00:34:09.423 --> 00:34:10.608
Hmm.

678
00:34:10.632 --> 00:34:13.051
I'll keep my eye out for his name.

679
00:34:14.136 --> 00:34:15.679
I'll do the same for yours.

680
00:34:21.477 --> 00:34:23.413
Are you kidding me?

681
00:34:23.437 --> 00:34:24.789
The studio was suing me.

682
00:34:24.813 --> 00:34:27.000
I've gone bankrupt because of this.

683
00:34:27.024 --> 00:34:30.378
I don't know what you're talking
about. but I'm-I'm so sorry...

684
00:34:30.402 --> 00:34:33.006
What's going on? Are the passed apps
not getting passed enough?

685
00:34:33.030 --> 00:34:35.216
I'm not sure.
The caterer recognized your mom

686
00:34:35.240 --> 00:34:37.719
-and started freaking out.
-Your hotshot husband destroyed my career.

687
00:34:37.743 --> 00:34:39.244
Oh. my God.

688
00:34:40.454 --> 00:34:42.098
That's my dad's botched nose job lady.

689
00:34:42.122 --> 00:34:43.266
I've had to take any job

690
00:34:43.290 --> 00:34:45.101
just to pay
for my reconstructive surgeries.

691
00:34:45.125 --> 00:34:47.645
He didn't bankrupt you.

692
00:34:47.669 --> 00:34:49.814
Your money problems were

693
00:34:49.838 --> 00:34:53.193
all over Page Six well before
you ever stepped foot into Wyatt's office.

694
00:34:53.217 --> 00:34:58.072
I made a few bad financial decisions. okay?

695
00:34:58.096 --> 00:34:59.783
But this isn't about the money.
They took away

696
00:34:59.807 --> 00:35:02.285
my cover of Soap Opera Digest.

697
00:35:02.309 --> 00:35:05.538
All right? They gave it to Kelly Ripa.
Kelly Ripa!

698
00:35:05.562 --> 00:35:07.582
You and I should have
a private conversation

699
00:35:07.606 --> 00:35:09.959
-somewhere.
-Oh. Oh. private.

700
00:35:09.983 --> 00:35:12.587
I'm so sorry. I'm being too loud for you.
I'm embarrassing you!

701
00:35:12.611 --> 00:35:13.880
I wonder what that feels like.

702
00:35:13.904 --> 00:35:16.090
I-I know that he made a mistake...

703
00:35:16.114 --> 00:35:17.759
A mistake.

704
00:35:17.783 --> 00:35:19.928
This is more than a mistake. okay?
He ruined my life.

705
00:35:19.952 --> 00:35:21.846
This is bad.

706
00:35:21.870 --> 00:35:23.097
Please.

707
00:35:23.121 --> 00:35:24.432
-come on.
-I'm-I'm not going to cause a scene.

708
00:35:24.456 --> 00:35:26.518
-She's fine.
-I just want to talk to her. I...

709
00:35:26.542 --> 00:35:29.479
I... I'm fine. You're a monster!

710
00:35:29.503 --> 00:35:30.838
Monster!

711
00:35:31.922 --> 00:35:33.316
I don't know. She's. you know...

712
00:35:33.340 --> 00:35:37.845
Uh. I mean. I think her anger issues
probably cost her her career.

713
00:35:39.054 --> 00:35:44.494
That's sad. And-and not Wyatt's
very minor mistake. Jordan. Um...

714
00:35:44.518 --> 00:35:48.790
But in-in some ways. some-some might say
that Wyatt actually helped her career

715
00:35:48.814 --> 00:35:51.459
because I don't know
that she should have done that soap cover.

716
00:35:51.483 --> 00:35:55.255
This nose might have opened up her career.
She could be

717
00:35:55.279 --> 00:35:57.090
smelling success.

718
00:35:57.114 --> 00:35:58.925
Hey. Hey. Hey. Hi.

719
00:35:58.949 --> 00:36:00.468
Hey. hey. are-are you all right?

720
00:36:00.492 --> 00:36:02.804
My dad's PR person can make this
go away like that.

721
00:36:02.828 --> 00:36:04.722
-Okay.
-Just say the word.

722
00:36:04.746 --> 00:36:05.807
Word.

723
00:36:05.831 --> 00:36:09.644
Okay. Uh. maybe I can
talk to my mom alone for a second?

724
00:36:09.668 --> 00:36:10.961
Of course.

725
00:36:13.755 --> 00:36:15.233
-Hey. hey. hey.
-Excuse me. sir.

726
00:36:15.257 --> 00:36:17.026
What... what are you...
what are you going to do?

727
00:36:17.050 --> 00:36:18.695
I don't know.

728
00:36:18.719 --> 00:36:20.488
I think I'm gonna send her flowers

729
00:36:20.512 --> 00:36:22.407
-tomorrow morning. and hope...
-Okay.

730
00:36:22.431 --> 00:36:23.992
That everything will be okay.

731
00:36:24.016 --> 00:36:27.245
I just... I feel like
we keep running away from our problems

732
00:36:27.269 --> 00:36:29.914
instead of facing them head-on.

733
00:36:29.938 --> 00:36:34.794
You and Dad. Me and...
basically everyone in Seattle.

734
00:36:34.818 --> 00:36:35.986
Okay.

735
00:36:38.071 --> 00:36:39.799
What if we went back?

736
00:36:39.823 --> 00:36:42.468
L.A. is an easy fix to a hard problem.

737
00:36:42.492 --> 00:36:43.636
Sweetie.

738
00:36:43.660 --> 00:36:47.664
And-and something I'm realizing is.
I miss doing things the hard way.

739
00:36:49.333 --> 00:36:51.769
Seattle has friction.

740
00:36:51.793 --> 00:36:54.671
And-and I think I need that.

741
00:36:56.298 --> 00:37:01.720
Fashion will always be here for me.
but I still have a lot of life to learn.

742
00:37:05.641 --> 00:37:06.910
I know you just got your life back.

743
00:37:06.934 --> 00:37:09.037
Let's do it.

744
00:37:09.061 --> 00:37:10.705
-Really?
-Yeah.

745
00:37:10.729 --> 00:37:12.206
I think it's a great idea.

746
00:37:12.230 --> 00:37:13.625
Let's go.

747
00:37:13.649 --> 00:37:16.669
And I have some...

748
00:37:16.693 --> 00:37:19.655
friction that I need to face. too.

749
00:37:20.739 --> 00:37:23.259
Uh. maybe... tomorrow?

750
00:37:23.283 --> 00:37:24.886
-Okay.
-Yeah.

751
00:37:24.910 --> 00:37:26.679
What about... what about
the Golden Globes?

752
00:37:26.703 --> 00:37:28.473
Well. there's this thing
called an Informal

753
00:37:28.497 --> 00:37:30.666
in Seattle I think I'd rather be at.

754
00:37:31.583 --> 00:37:32.584
Okay.

755
00:37:33.669 --> 00:37:35.605
Oh. there's. um...

756
00:37:35.629 --> 00:37:37.315
there's just one more thing I need to do.

757
00:37:37.339 --> 00:37:38.674
Okay.

758
00:37:54.856 --> 00:37:56.250
Who are we spying on?

759
00:37:56.274 --> 00:37:59.879
Mm. I thought these agents
would have some good gossip.

760
00:37:59.903 --> 00:38:03.466
but it's just a boring story
about Mr. Holland's Opus.

761
00:38:03.490 --> 00:38:04.908
Hmm.

762
00:38:06.284 --> 00:38:08.304
How is she?

763
00:38:08.328 --> 00:38:10.539
She'll be okay.

764
00:38:13.792 --> 00:38:15.627
And are you still hiding from Josh?

765
00:38:17.587 --> 00:38:19.047
Not actively.

766
